race.comment: Over to the Cup where all eyes will be on GILDED WATER (7). He bolted on Jamie Melham in the G3 Bart Cummings at Flemington when going out far too hard in front. The effort to stick on for third was outstanding. If Bates can control him early he should be winning. TORRANZINO (4) was excellent in the Bart Cummings when chasing that fast pace at a big price. Clearly relished a staying trip there and a repeat of it goes close. WHISKY ON THE HILL (5) was desperately unlucky in the Herbert Power but that wasn't the strongest race. BERKELEY SQUARE (2) was good in the Bart Cummings and is in the mix.
